# Production Environment Variables
PORT=4000
NODE_ENV=production
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secure-secret-key-change-this-in-production-min-256-bits
CLIENT_URL=https://www.hellversechat.com
CORS_ORIGIN=https://www.hellversechat.com

# Email Configuration - Auto-detects provider from EMAIL_USER domain
# Supported providers: Gmail, Outlook, Hotmail, Yahoo, iCloud, AOL, Zoho, ProtonMail
# Just provide EMAIL_USER and EMAIL_PASS - SMTP settings are automatic!
#
# EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com          # Your email address
# EMAIL_PASS=your-app-password             # Your email app password (NOT regular password)
#
# Optional manual SMTP override (if auto-detection doesn't work):
# EMAIL_HOST=smtp.custom-provider.com      # SMTP server hostname
# EMAIL_PORT=587                           # SMTP port (usually 587 or 465)
#
# Setup Instructions by Provider:
# 
# Gmail:
#   1. Enable 2-factor authentication
#   2. Generate "App Password" at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#   3. Use: EMAIL_USER=yourname@gmail.com EMAIL_PASS=app-password
#
# Outlook/Hotmail:
#   1. Enable 2-factor authentication
#   2. Generate "App Password" in security settings
#   3. Use: EMAIL_USER=yourname@outlook.com EMAIL_PASS=app-password
#
# Yahoo:
#   1. Enable 2-factor authentication
#   2. Generate "App Password" in account security
#   3. Use: EMAIL_USER=yourname@yahoo.com EMAIL_PASS=app-password
#
# iCloud:
#   1. Enable 2-factor authentication
#   2. Generate "App-Specific Password" at appleid.apple.com
#   3. Use: EMAIL_USER=yourname@icloud.com EMAIL_PASS=app-password

# Database (for future use)
# DATABASE_URL=your-database-connection-string